  "usage": {
    "title": "Getting started",
    "step1": "Click “Add connection”, fill in host / port / credentials. Defaults match a vanilla Docker `rabbitmq:management` image (guest/guest, ports 5672/15672).",
    "step2": "Use “Test connection” — it calls /api/overview via the management plugin (port 15672) to confirm credentials and that the management plugin is enabled.",
    "step3": "Switch vhost on the top bar to scope topology lookups; the “(all)” option queries the unfiltered endpoints.",
    "step4": "Peek pulls messages with basic.get + reject(requeue=true); your broker copy is unchanged. Turn requeue OFF if you intentionally want to drain.",
    "step5": "Publish uses lapin with publisher confirms. The default AMQP exchange routes by queue name in the routing key.",
    "close": "Close",
    "note": "lapin handles AMQP framing; topology + purge/delete go through the RabbitMQ Management HTTP API."
  }
